The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM `loop-vectorize` pass.
The crash is an assertion failure in `LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF`:
`Assertion (BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width || planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(BestFactor.Width), CostCtx, OrigLoop)) && " VPlan cost model and legacy cost model disagreed"' failed.`

This indicates a discrepancy between the legacy cost model and the VPlan-native cost model for loop vectorization. The VPlan model chose a vectorization factor (VF) that the legacy model did not, and the `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` check failed to justify this difference.

The reproducer IR contains a branch on a constant `br i1 false, ...`. This makes one path in the loop dead. The PHI node in the latch block (`%p`) has an incoming value from this dead path. The VPlan infrastructure is likely simplifying this dead path away, leading to a different cost estimation compared to the legacy path which might not perform the same simplification.

The `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` function is intended to account for such differences. It checks for things like simplified PHIs. The problem is that the PHI node `%p` is in the latch block. The current implementation of `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` iterates over PHIs in the loop header, but not in other blocks of the loop.

The fix is to extend `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` to check for simplified PHIs in all blocks of the loop, not just the header. This will correctly identify that the VPlan has performed a simplification (by constant-folding the PHI `%p` due to the dead path), which will then satisfy the assertion and allow the vectorization to proceed based on the VPlan's more accurate cost assessment.

I will modify `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp` to change the loop that iterates over PHIs. Instead of `for (PHINode &PH : OrigLoop->getHeader()->phis())`, I will iterate through all blocks in the loop and then through the PHIs in each block.

```cpp
// Original code in planContainsAdditionalSimplifications:
for (PHINode &PH : OrigLoop->getHeader()->phis()) {
  // ...
}

// Proposed change:
for (BasicBlock *BB : OrigLoop->getBlocks()) {
  for (PHINode &PH : BB->phis()) {
    // ...
  }
}
```

This change will make the check more comprehensive and should resolve the assertion failure.

```bash
